<iframe width="560" height="560" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/d32CcprU4N4" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen=""></iframe>

<p>The grease pencil tool (that basically allows you do draw in the 3D space) upgraded in blender 2.8 was of great use to draw details on surfaces. I learned a lot from analysing <a href="https://cloud.blender.org/p/gallery/5e46a80442fa9613e1cd1fca">Dedouze‚Äôs 2.82 splash screen file</a>.</p>

